      "body" : "> /rest/tx being always the latest (v1 atm)\r\n\r\nAbsolute NACK on that, you cant have APIs upgrading themselves to new versions. Consumers explicitly address the version they need. `/rest/tx` can only become a legacy path to be deprecated, or remain forever an alias for `/rest/v1/tx`.",
